    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nTake the following example:\n```cython\ncdef void example():\n    cdef extern void* c_function()\n    cdef void* result = c_function()\n```\n\nThis will fail to compile with Cython 3.0.12 and latest master because there is no forward declaration for `c_function`. This only happens if `cdef extern void* c_function()` is inside of a function, if it is outside everything is gucci.\nSame result with a `cdef extern from *` block.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\ncdef void example():\n    cdef extern void* c_function()\n    cdef void* result = c_function()\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nCython should generate a forward declaration for `c_function`\n\n### OS\n\nWindows\n\n### Python version\n\n3.13.0\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.0.12, master\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
