            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">I think it should probably be rejected as an error by Cython instead.\n\nYes, definitely. It makes no sense at all to allow C includes, verbatim C code, or extern declarations inside of a function context. Cython cannot control code injected into a function this way, potentially leading to arbitrary conflicts with exception handling or type inference assumptions. So the effect would always have to be global, which means that a global declaration is the right place.\n",
